ion on all that Lexington has to offer  including lodging  may be found at the Lexington and Rockbridge Area Tourism site  Below are area hotels that have offered blocks of rooms for the 2016 Virginia State Science and Engineering Fair  Please note that some of them will release those room blocks as much as 30 days prior to the event  Book early to reserve these rates  NOTE  Remember that family and friends of Fair exhibitors must leave the hall once judging begins  Many shops and stores downtown do not open until 10am  We  therefore  recommend you drop off the student contestant at Cameron Hall and check out afterwards  but prior to the hotel s required check out time    Hotel  Rate Phone   Toll Free  800  Best Western Inn at Hunt Ridge  89 00  540  464 1500   800  464 1501 Comfort Inn Virginia Horse Center  89 00  540  463 7311   Howard Johnson s Inn Lexington  65 95  540  463 9181   R  E  Lee Hotel  89 00  540  461 8484   Sleep Inn Hotel   Suites  69 00  540  463 6000       Attendees requiring handicapped accessibility or other assistance are encouraged to contact Mrs  Ronda Dove at  540  464 7361 for information and coordination   Directions to Cameron Hall From Interstate 81  take Exit 188B toward US 60 W E Midland Trail Merge onto US 60 W E Midland Trail Continue to follow US 60 W Turn right onto S Lewis St  Take the 1st right onto N Lewis St  Take the 3rd left onto Diamond St  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions